<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870527-0145 </DOCNO><HL> National Gas andamp; Oil Co. Unit</HL><DD> 05/27/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> NLG CYLTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> NEWARK, Ohio  </DATELINE><TEXT>   National Gas andamp; Oil Co. said its National Production Corp. unit and Levengood Oil andamp; Gas (U.S.) Inc. have formed a new company to acquire energy properties and explore for natural gas and oil.    National Gas said the concern, to be called Roscoe Gas andamp; Oil Co., will be held equally by National Production and Dover, Ohio-based Levengood. Roscoe's first acquisition will be pipelines and 129 oil and gas wells in Ohio and Pennsylvania owned by Pittsburgh-based Cyclops Corp. Terms weren't disclosed. </TEXT></DOC>